                                <span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_JobDetails2_lblDescription" class="jobDetail_jobDesc_Content"><p>O365 Data Protection Manager    Responsible for all aspects of O365 Data Protection Direct Management of 6 Direct Reports.    Including Service delivery management, tools management &amp; escalation. Responsible for the Customer communication pertaining to any NTK’s.    Where volume &amp; security level is within scope    Management of the O365 data Protection Service Delivery team. <br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>30+ team currently based out of Costa Rica    Defining Strategy &amp; Scope for the Service Delivery team to ensure the team deliver against the KPI’s defined &amp; offer a white glove service to our Microsoft Customers Overall responsibility of O365 tools management &amp; adherence to any required audit requirements. Being the voice of security for all O365 related issues Main areas of delivery include:<br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>-      Governing administrative access and resolving domain/identity issues for customers <br></p>
<p>-      Customer recovery related to data protection incidents (Microsoft or customer detected) <br></p>
<p>-      Protecting Microsoft against known and emerging security vulnerabilities related to access to customer data         <br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Key Stakeholders: External: Office 365 Customers (Multi-Tenant SMB, Dedicated, Education, Concierge) Internal: Frontline Support (EXO, Azure, Identity Cloud), CELA, PG/Engineering, Modern Support (Concierge), TAM / Sales, Fast Track Center, GetHelp, IPG    <br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Basic Qualifications:<br></p>
<p>•      3 years+ of Customer Service experience <br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Preferred Qualifications:<br></p>
<p>•      Educated to degree level <br></p>
<p>•      Proven experience within O365 Data Protection    <br></p>
<p>•      Previous Management experience<br></p>
<p><br></p>
